rComments: Excellent teacher, so it really sucks that he got fired.  Explained principles very well and made the class fun for everyone.  Even though I didn't get an A in the class, I still learned a lot and wish he could teach me again.  Best teacher I've had at college.
He's is being fired following this semester which is frankly a disgrace.  He is one of my favorite professors I've ever had.  The University is losing a truly gifted teacher

I had him for Psych 100 and he was very clear with everything he taught. This was by far my favorite course so far in college, probably because Eugene was so amazing as a teacher. Very good-looking too! Take a class with him! You'll do well if you put in effort and you'll have a good time too.

He's super helpful in lecture notes, and his quizzes and grading policy is pretty easy. He is great eye candy, and has an awesome sense of humor, so this class was pretty fun, and he was really cool about letting class out early sometimes and giving out treats...even though he was quite a treat himself...:) haha awesome teacher!
He made us take a lot of notes but I think it's because he really wants us to do well.  And he's great eye candy- that sure spiced up the class!

He tries his hardest to make lectures interesting, and when I was getting ready for finals, he let me sit in his office and look at old exams for practice.  My only complaint is that sometimes the quiz questions were a little opaque, but I suppose that's just psychology for you.
best professor I've had at college. he's funny as ****ing hell
He has a good grading policy...and I think he tries his best to make lectures interesting, but I'm not much into that stuff so I didn't like the class too much.
